                  </hi>. I live in Chichester-place, Gray's Inn-road, and am a haberdasher. These slippers are mine—I had them safe at my door on the 1st of August—I was taking the things in, and a gentleman said, "A boy has taken a pair of shoes"—I saw the prisoner, and followed him, crying, "Stop thief"—he jumped down an area—a policeman came up and caught him—I asked him where the shoes were—he said, "The shoes are down where I came from, if you will go down for them"—the policeman got them—these are them.</p>
